# For details, see http://www.timj.co.uk/linux/sa.php
cd /etc/mail/spamassassin
sudo wget http://www.timj.co.uk/linux/bogus-virus-warnings.cf

Periodically run these commands (possibly on even more mailboxes):
      sa-learn --showdots --mbox --spam $HOME/.mail/sa-spam.mail
      sa-learn --showdots --mbox --ham $HOME/.mail/sa-ham.mail
[I need a huge ham folder in Unix mail format; how to do this?]

On pag, run "spamassassin -D --lint" and keep an eye out for lines like:
  debug: bayes: Not available for scanning, DB_File not installed
  debug: bayes: Not available for scanning, only 0 spam(s) in Bayes DB < 200

